,Recommended,431710,34675459,Posted: 1 September,all,Kuzhara,"Epsilon Indi is the second part in a four part saga, as mentioned in my previous review for Alpha Centauri.Once again you take control of the Quicksilver, piloted by Gail Pilgrim. There are new characters, as well as a few old ones. One of the good thing that this saga did right was the character development over the series. It helps you become more attached to the story and characters, in my opinion. This one, as well as the third one, went more in depth with the story of the Pilgrim universe.Epsilon Indi is, like its predecessor, filled with puzzles that you have to solve in order to advance, as well as filled with a few twists of its own to keep things interesting.An enjoyable puzzle and adventure RPG, however it's not without its flaws, concerning the length of the game. Like I mentioned in my other review, this one should only take about a few hours to complete, and that's why I'm rating this sequel another 8/10."
